3. Enable full change and run ETL; capture counts.
4. Produce reconciliation comparing baseline vs post-change counts and sample diffs.","No net unexpected losses of records occur outside the intended inclusion of IRCA records; the delta is explainable by the intended behavior change. If delta exceeds threshold (configurable), fail and investigate.","temp_word_images/image3.png","Covers AC-001.4"

"TC-CSR-233-POS-002","TS-CSR-233-002","CSR-233","POS","High","Access to data field `pc_policylocation.stateinternal` and `pctl_state` typelist mapping in staging DB.","1. Identify sample policies with vehicles located in various provinces (QC, BC, ON, etc.).
