3. Run mapping logic that converts `stateinternal` to two-letter code via `pctl_state.typecode`.
4. Verify `risk_province` assigned in result set matches expected two-letter code.","`risk_province` for each sample equals the `pctl_state.typecode` corresponding to `pc_policylocation.stateinternal`. QC and BC cases are correctly mapped and appear in the IRCA inclusion results.","temp_word_images/image1.png","Validates AC-002.1 and AC-002.2"

"TC-CSR-233-NEG-002","TS-CSR-233-002","CSR-233","NEG","High","Staging data that includes records with null, empty, or malformed `stateinternal` values.","1. Prepare sample records with null `stateinternal`, empty string, and malformed values.
